  "response": "Travancore (or Thiruvithamkoor in Malayalam) was a princely state located in the southern part of present-day Kerala, in southwestern India. After India's independence, Travancore merged with the princely state of Cochin and later became part of Kerala state when it was formed in 1956. The region is now part of Kerala state, primarily covering the southern districts including Thiruvananthapuram (the state capital), Kollam, Alappuzha, and parts of Pathanamthitta district.",
